Lene Name Meaning, Origin & Details

Meaning: Woman from Magdala Short Info: In Greek mythology Helen was the daughter of Zeus and Leda, whose kidnapping by Paris was the cause of the Trojan War. Details: A pet form of Helena, from the Greek Helene, meaning "torch", or "corposant", another name for St Elmo's fire. Gender: Girl Origin: Danish, Hebrew Religion: Christian Suitable for: Girls / Female / Women Hardness: Easy to pronounce, Lene is a short name Uniqueness: It is a common name Short & Easy: Yes Syllables: 4 Letters and 1 Words
